This template accepts these parameters:
:{{para|id{{var|n}}}} – a SBN identifier; the {{para|id{{var|n}}}} parameter name is not required but is recommended for clarity when the template has multiple SBNs
:{{para|link}} – accepts a single value <code>no</code>; for use when the 'SBN' prefix in the rendering should not be linked
:{{para|plainlink}} – accepts a single value <code>yes</code>; suppresses the 'SBN' prefix in the rendering
:{{para|leadout}} – defines the conjunction between the last two identifiers in the rendered list; defaults to <code>, </code>
The basic form is:
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|340-01381-8}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|340-01381-8}}
For multiple SBNs:
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|340-01381-8|340-01381-8|340-01381-8}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|340-01381-8|340-01381-8|340-01381-8}}
To unlink the prefix:
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|340-01381-8|link=no}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|340-01381-8|link=no}}
To suppress the prefix:
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|340-01381-8|plainlink=yes}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|340-01381-8|plainlink=yes}}
To use <code>and</code> between the last two identifiers in the rendered list:
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|340-01381-8|340-01381-8|340-01381-8|leadout=and}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|340-01381-8|340-01381-8|340-01381-8|leadout=and}}
When this template emits an error message for a valid (working) SBN, use the accept-as-written markup <code>((..))</code> to suppress the error message.
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|340-01381-0}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|340-01381-0}}
:<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline="1">{{SBN|((340-01381-0))}}</syntaxhighlight> → {{SBN|((340-01381-0))}}

==Tracking categories==
*{{cl|Ignored ISBN errors}} – {{color|#18911f|maintenance}} category for {{tld|SBN}} templates using the accept-as-written markup <code>((..))</code> to suppress an error message – shared with {{tlx|ISBN}}
*{{cl|Pages with SBN errors}} – {{color|#d33|error}} category for {{tld|ISBN}} templates that show an error message

Because this template uses the same code as cs1|2 templates, {{color|#d33|error}} and {{color|#18911f|maintenance}} visibility is controlled the same way.  See {{slink|Help:CS1_errors|Controlling_error_message_display}}.

===See also===
